ow lentil, also known as split pigeon peas) are both available at Indian food stores or online.","Clean and scrape down the roots of your coriander with a spoon to remove the tougher, more fibrous bits on the outside of the roots, before adding to the mixing bowl.","When adding mint leaves to mixing bowl, be sure to add it in big handfuls, as the weight of individual leaves may not register on the scales.","To save time, rinse, drain and soak dal first. Then make curry paste and store in the refrigerator until ready to use the next day when cooking remainder of recipe.","You can store this paste in the refrigerator for up to 5 days or in the freezer for up to 1 month.","You can serve this with your favourite side. We served ours with Garlic and coriander naan. Please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","26h","6 portions"]}